commText: Head and Abhishek Sharma are at the crease. Head is on strike. Khaleel Ahmed will open the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Head, no run, flashes at the very first one and misses, fairly full and wide outside off, was there to be hit and Head threw his hands at it but missed

Khaleel Ahmed to Head, SIX, he doesn't miss the second one! Friendly length outside off, a proper half-tracker and Head sat back in his crease, waited for it and pumped it over wide long-on with a pull, that's too easy for Travis Head

Khaleel Ahmed to Head, FOUR, SMASHED! You give him width and you'll only see it disappear! A length delivery with a hint of width outside off, Head flashed hard at it again and it raced to the point fence

Khaleel Ahmed to Head, FOUR, nearly all the way too! Wrong length again, just in that nothing zone, Head stands still and tall in his crease before heaving it away flat over mid-wicket, just bounces inside the ropes, oh boy is this a sign of things to come?

Khaleel Ahmed to Head, 1 run, finally gets one right, Khaleel Ahmed goes full and at the pads, bit of shape and Head missed his flick, thud into the pad and went into the off-side, just a stifled appeal for leg before but it was heading down leg

Khaleel Ahmed to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, oh dear, that makes it 19 off the over! Loses his radar again does Khaleel, on a length and drifting down leg, all Abhishek Sharma had to do was help it on its way down to the fine-leg ropes, cracking start for SRH again
Lalit Yadav, right-arm off break, comes into the attack

Lalit Yadav to Head, SIX, there is no stopping Travis Head! Length delivery on middle, angles in and Head was so quick to rock back and pull it away over the deep mid-wicket ropes, made it look so easy

Lalit Yadav to Head, SIX, nearly an action replay but this one goes further! Almost the same delivery and exactly the same result, flatter and into the deck on middle, Head presses back and heaves it away over deep mid-wicket once again
Lalit Yadav to Head, no run, floated up full and straight, only pushed back to the bowler this time

Lalit Yadav to Head, FOUR, crashed through the off-side this time! Flatter and width on offer outside off, Head doesn't need second invitations to slap this away through the cover-point region for another boundary, fielder got a hand to it but it didn't do much
Lalit Yadav to Head, 1 run, full and on the pads, worked away to deep mid-wicket

Lalit Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, FOUR, an assault from both ends! Abhishek Sharma is never one to be left too far behind, he gets one in his zone, full and wide outside off and he lofts it over extra cover, didn't hit it cleanly but it almost went the distance
Anrich Nortje, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Nortje to Head, FOUR, it's like batting practice this! Head is making this pitch look so true, full and straight on middle, Head cleared his front-leg and lofted this one clean through the line and over mid-on, one bounce and four

Nortje to Head, FOUR, the edge but the result doesn't change! Full and straight on middle again, Head cleared his front-leg again and slogged across the line this time, he got a thick inside edge that raced down past short fine-leg
Nortje to Head, no run, banged in short on middle, Head ducks under the bouncer

Nortje to Head, FOUR, 50 partnership comes up in no time! This length isn't working for DC, the bounce is so true and anything on this good length, Head is trusting the bounce and heaving it away, this time he finds the gap at mid-wicket with precision
Nortje to Head, FOUR, how do you stop this man? Full and straight on middle-leg, Head makes a bit of room, opens the face of the bat and slices it away past backward point for another boundary!

Nortje to Head, SIX, Head brings up 50 in 16 balls! Brutal, absolutely brutal this from Head and he's been doing it all season long! Full and straight, on the pads this time and he picked it up and deposited it over the deep mid-wicket ropes, joint-fastest 50 of the season and the man who shares the record is at the other end!

Lalit Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, DC, it's going to be a long night! Length delivery on middle, Abhishek Sharma stands stiil, waits for it and heaves it away over deep mid-wicket, short boundaries and it just about goes over
Most time scoring 50+ in Powerplay in IPL 6 - David Warner 3 - Chris Gayle 3 - Sunil Narine 3 - Travis Head*
Lalit Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, leg byes, 1 run, flatter and quicker angled into leg-stump, Abhishek Sharma looks to pull it fine, goes towards short fine-leg off the thigh pad
Lalit Yadav to Head, 1 run, tossed up slow and full on middle, low full-toss and Head pushes it back to the bowler who moves to his left and fails to stop it, single conceded to mid-on

Lalit Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, boot up Cricket 07 and you still probably can't replicate this! This batting is unreal! Flat and into the pitch, Abhishek Sharma runs down the wicket and smacks it away over wide long-on again
Lalit Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, very full on off-stump, Abhishek Sharma mistimes it towards square leg for a single

Lalit Yadav to Head, SIX, still counting? Length delivery on off-stump, Head hangs back and smacks it up and over the bowler's head, his weight wasn't even going into the shot and it still goes over long-off comfortably!

Fastest IPL fifties for SRH (by balls taken) 16 - Abhishek Shamra vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 16 - Travis Head vs DC, Delhi, today* 18 - Travis Head vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 20 - David Warner vs CSK, Hyderabad, 2015 20 - David Warner vs KKR, Hyderabad, 2017

No words left and we're just in the 4th over! DC would've expected a barrage but this is shocking. It's unreal to see the ease at which they're hitting these boundaries. Now can Kuldeep Yadav have a say?
Kuldeep Yadav, comes into the attack

Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, no he can't, he absolutely can't! Kuldeep gets the customary welcome, tossed up full on middle-leg, Abhishek Sharma runs down the track and lofts it over long-on with absolute ease

Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, back to back! Flatter on middle-leg, Abhishek Sharma presses back this time and pulls it away over deep mid-wicket, absolutely everything is hitting the middle of the bat and sailing over the ropes
Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, good length delivery on leg-stump, Abhishek Sharma comes down the track and pushes it down the ground to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Head, no run, length delivery wide outside off, bit of turn, Head presses back looking to cut and chops it back towards Pant off a thick bottom edge, a rare dot ball
Kuldeep Yadav to Head, 1 run, touch fuller and at the pads, skids through and hits the pad as Head looks to glance it fine, they get a leg bye to square leg

Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, 100 up in 5 overs! You read that right! Length delivery on leg-stump, Abhishek Sharma runs down the track again, doesn't get anywhere near the pitch of it but he still sends it into orbit over deep mid-wicket
Fastest fifty in terms of team overs in IPL 2.5 - Yashasvi Jaiswal vs KKR, 2023 2.5 - KL Rahul vs DC, 2018 3.0 - Travis Head vs DC, 2024*

Highlights (Overs 1-5) -> Khaleel concedes 19 runs in his first over, Head smashes him -> Lalit goes for 21 runs in his opening over -> SRH off to a flying start, 50 up in the 3rd over -> Head brings up his fifty in 16 balls -> First 5 overs - 19,21,22,21,20
If they continue at this rate, SRH can get 400. Yes, not 300 but 400. WOW
Mukesh Kumar, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Mukesh Kumar to Head, FOUR, now Mukesh Kumar is greeted with a boundary! He runs in from round the wicket, goes fairly full and just outside off, angles in but Head clears his front-leg and absolutely smashes it through extra cover
Mukesh Kumar to Head, FOUR, this is bullying! Length delivery just outside off, Head stays leg-side again, sees it so well and slaps it up and over extra cover this time

Fastest team hundreds in IPL history (by overs taken) 5 overs - SRH vs DC, Delhi, today* 6 overs - CSK vs PBKS, Mumbai WS, 2014 6 overs - KKR vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2017 6.5 overs - CSK vs MI, Mumbai WS, 2015 7 overs - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024

Mukesh Kumar to Head, FOUR, poor bowling, he's got the field up on the off-side but he goes short and wide outside off, so much pressure and DC are playing into SRH's hands, too easy for Head as he slaps it up and over cover, one-bounce four

Mukesh Kumar to Head, FOUR, four fours in a row! The novelty is wearing off, it seriously is with every ball going either to or over the ropes, very full on middle, went for the yorker and just undercooked it a touch, Head cleared his front-leg and drilled it straight back through the bowler
Mukesh Kumar to Head, no run, and a dot, take a breath, length delivery angled into the pads, Head looked to heave this away over square leg and missed

Mukesh Kumar to Head, SIX, this one goes all the way! DC already seem to be losing the plot, this is a juicy half-volley on off-stump from Mukesh Kumar, even the good balls have traveled so no surprise this goes over the ropes at long-off

TIMEOUT! Boy if ever DC needed a timeout it's now. SRH have scored at will in a very literal sense. How do DC stop this? Every bowler has gone the distance so far. Great pitch, short boundaries and SRH - absolute carnage!

Highest powerplay scores in the IPL 125/0 - SRH vs DC, 2024* 105/0 - KKR vs RCB, 2017 100/2 - CSK vs PBKS, 2014 90/0 - CSK vs MI, 2015 88/1 - KKR vs DC, 2024* This is also the highest powerplay score in T20 cricket

Highest scores in the PP for SRH in the IPL 84 (26) - Travis Head vs DC, Delhi, today* 62*(25) - David Warner vs KKR, Hyderabad, 2019 59*(20) - Travis Head vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 59*(23) - David Warner vs CSK, Hyderabad, 2015 * Only Suresh Raina (87 vs PBKS in 2024) has scored more runs in PP than Travis Head

Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, back to business! Floated up full and straight on middle, Abhishek Sharma skips down the track, he was beaten in by the flight but went through with the shot, hit the toe end but still went 84m back over the bowler's head
Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Axar!! Now then, Abhishek Sharma holes out! Just misses out on another record fifty. Kuldeep Yadav gets the breakthrough but my word, no one has probably hit 12 balls they've faced much better. Tossed up full and just outside off, Abhishek Sharma presses forward looking to drill it through extra cover but he doesn't keep it down, Axar the man leapt to his left and took a very sharp catch. Was traveling fast and low but Axar held on. Abhishek Sharma c Axar b Kuldeep Yadav 46(12) [4s-2 6s-6]
Aiden Markram, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kuldeep Yadav to Markram, 1 run, length delivery on middle, Markram presses back and pushes it down the ground to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Head, 1 run, tossed up full just outside off, Head leans in looking for a slog-sweep, he mistimes it down to wide long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Markram, no run, tossed up full on leg-stump, Markram opens the face of the bat and steers it to cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Markram, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Markram, out Caught by Axar!! One brings two! This is exactly what the Capitals would've wished for, hoped for and prayed for at the break! Length delivery outside off, it was the googly and Markram didn't pick it, expected it to come in but it went away, he was just caught there with his bat hung out and it went straight Axar again at extra cover. Only a wicket could halt this assault, Kuldeep says how about two! Markram c Axar b Kuldeep Yadav 1(3)
Abhishek Sharma vs Kuldeep Yadav 3 inns 13 balls 38 runs two dismissals 19.0 avg 292.3 SR
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Axar to Head, 1 run, length delivery outside off, slapped away to deep cover
Axar to Klaasen, 1 run, flatter delivery angling into off-stump, Klaasen backs away a little and cuts it towards point before pinching a sharp single
Axar to Head, 1 run, full on middle, pushed down the ground to long on

Axar to Klaasen, 1 run, flatter delivery angling into the stumps again, Klaasen looked to punch that through the covers but it skidded through, took a thick inside edge and went towards backward square leg
Axar to Head, 1 run, length delivery outside off, punched down to long-off
Axar to Klaasen, no run, flatter delivery wide outside off, Klaasen hangs back looking to cut and misses, an over without a boundary! It almost feels surreal after that blitz
Kuldeep Yadav to Head, 1 run, length delivery on leg-stump, Head presses back and makes a bit of room, punches it back towards Kuldeep who misfields and lets it through for a single down to long-off

Kuldeep Yadav to Klaasen, SIX, in case you were just starting to forget who's running the show! Floated up full and on middle, right in the zone for Klaasen and he smokes it straight back over the bowler's head

Kuldeep Yadav to Klaasen, no run, DC review and it's lost. It was for caught behind and they wanted to just be sure Klaasen hadn't gotten a little tickle on this. Was flat and sliding across just outside off, Klaasen looked to cut and missed, nothing on UltraEdge and Klaasen will go on

Kuldeep Yadav to Klaasen, SIX, yep, right on cue! Floated up full on middle, Klaasen leans in and slogs it a long way over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. SRH might well have a mini-game going on about who can hit the most sixes
A little halt in play as the ball is taking it's time to come back from the stands. Gives Kuldeep and Rishabh a chance to have another chat
Kuldeep Yadav to Klaasen, wide, tough, very tough for a bowler, flatter and pushed across outside off, just passes the line
Kuldeep Yadav to Klaasen, 1 run, fired in fast and straight on a length, pushed down to long-off, that was bowled at 114.5kph
Kuldeep Yadav to Head, wide, length delivery wide outside off, grips and turns away, beats Head who was looking to cut and ends up well outside the line
Kuldeep Yadav to Head, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Head, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! Kuldeep has a third! He's taking all the beating but is also biting back! Now Travis Head goes and it might just restore a bit of normalcy in this game. Was flat and just outside off, Head pressed back looking to heave it away over long-on, probably got to him just a little quicker than he expected and he couldn't get the elevation, he struck it flat and Stubbs took a nice catch running in. Head c Tristan Stubbs b Kuldeep Yadav 89(32) [4s-11 6s-6]
Nitish Reddy, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Axar to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Axar to Klaasen, out Bowled!! Now Delhi are really fighting back! Kuldeep and Axar are standing tall despite the barrage. Klaasen's out too. Flat and right at the stumps again, Klaasen pressed back and swung right across the line, he missed and Axar hit. All of a sudden, it's a completely different game. Four wickets down, two new batters and it might finally be the end of the carnage. Klaasen b Axar 15(8) [6s-2]
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, length delivery on off-stump, pushed towards mid-wicket
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, tossed up full and at the pads, Shahbaz Ahmed leans in and beats short fine-leg to his right with a sweep, deep backward square leg cleans up
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, flatter delivery just outside off, punched down the ground to long-on
Axar to Nitish Reddy, no run, length delivery on middle, Nitish Reddy presses back and bunts it back to the bowler's right
Axar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, length delivery on middle, worked away to deep square leg

Highlights (Overs 6-10) -> Kuldeep strikes, removes Abhishek and Markram in the same over -> Head looks to take on Kuldeep, gets caught at long-on -> Axar gets the big fish, Klaasen is clean bowled by a straighter one -> Sunrisers - 158/4 after 10 overs..

Halfway through and the projected score is 316 if SRH continue to score at this rate! But it does feel like the worst is behind them for DC, it's been an incredible fightback from Axar and Kuldeep. They kept their heads on their shoulder, didn't get flustered amidst the blitz and they've brought their team back into the contest.
Highest scores after first 10 overs in IPL 158/4 - SRH vs DC, Delhi, today* 148/2 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 141/2 - MI vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2024 135/1 - KKR vs DC, Vizag, 2024
Anrich Nortje [1.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Nortje to Nitish Reddy, no run, full on off-stump, pushed towards mid-on
Nortje to Nitish Reddy, no run, slower length delivery just outside off, Nitish Reddy moves around in his crease a little bit and misses after swinging for the hills
Shahbaz Ahmed immedietely comes down and has a word with his partner
Nortje to Nitish Reddy, wide, banged in short and going down leg, Nitish Reddy looks to pull it away but it was well down leg

Nortje to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, quick run! Length delivery on middle, Nitish Reddy tucked it towards mid-wicket and decided to take the fielder on, direct-hit at the non-striker's end and he was gone for all money!
Nortje to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length delivery on middle, hits the deck hard and Shahbaz Ahmed mistimes a pull towards mid-wicket
Nortje to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, full on off-stump, knocked down to long-on
Nortje to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, length delivery just outside off, eased towards backward point
Khaleel Ahmed [1.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack

Khaleel Ahmed to Nitish Reddy, FOUR, that's one for the photographers! Gorgeous shot! Pitched up full and just outside off from round the wicket, juicy half-volley and Nitish Reddy played a picture-perfect cover drive for four
Khaleel Ahmed to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, Nitish Reddy hangs back and eases it down to third man

Khaleel Ahmed to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, this is poor bowling and we're back amongst the boundaries! Short and wide outside off, easy pickings for Shahbaz Ahmed as he slapped it away up and over backward point, just about went over the ropes but it was in the gap anyway
Khaleel Ahmed to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, Shahbaz Ahmed gets on top of the bounce and pats it down towards backward point for one
Khaleel Ahmed to Nitish Reddy, no run, length delivery just outside off, punched straight to extra cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, tucked away towards wide long-on for one
Axar Patel [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Axar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, flatter delivery on off-stump, clipped away to deep mid-wicket
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length delivery angled wide outside off, Shahbaz Ahmed reaches out and slices it towards backward point, fielder gets a hand on it and it will only be one
Axar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, full on off-stump, pushed down to long-on
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, flatter delivery on leg-stump, worked away to deep mid-wicket

Axar to Nitish Reddy, FOUR, was in the air but in the gap! Length delivery angled into the pads, Nitish Reddy went deep in his crease and whipped it up in the air, he picked the gap at deep mid-wicket nicely though, one-bounce and four
Axar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, full on middle, Nitish Reddy leans in and works it away to deep mid-wicket

Timeout. Seems like we've just returned to Earth after travelling at light-speed. Don't know about you but my head is still buzzing from that onslaught. Nonetheless, has been fairly 'normal' cricket in the last few overs. Time for me to take a backseat, here's Pradeep for the rest of the innings.
Mukesh Kumar [1.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, punched off the back-foot to deep point for a single
Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, low full-toss from Mukesh, bowled from round the wicket, punched down to long-off for a single

Mukesh Kumar to Nitish Reddy, SIX, massive, length ball angling into the right-hander, Nitish leans across, brings his wrists into play and then muscles the whip over wide long-on, sailed deep into the crowd
Mukesh Kumar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, the slower cutter from Mukesh, worked through mid-wicket for a single
Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, pushed in front of cover for a single
Mukesh Kumar to Nitish Reddy, no run, the yorker from Mukesh, Nitish jams his bat down and squeezes an under-edge onto the pad
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, flatter and angling across the left-hander, punched to the left of point for a single
Axar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, quicker and flatter from Axar, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, chopped square on the off-side for a single
Axar to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, pushed through by Axar as Nitish came down the pitch, punched down to long-off for a single

Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, nicely played, tossed up quicker by Axar, but the line is down leg - Shahbaz gets inside the line and then sweeps it overfine leg who was inside the ring, lobs over the ropes for a maximum
Axar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, dragged short and wide of off, punched down to long-off for a single

Highlights (Overs 11-15) -> Nortje bowls an economical over, concedes only 4 runs -> Nitish and Shahbaz take on Khaleel, another productive over -> A steady partnership building for the fifth wicket -> 200 up for Sunrisers in the 15th over
Anrich Nortje [2.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack

Nortje to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, back of a length and angling across the left-hander, Shahbaz makes most of the pace as he ran it towards third man, needed a big dive from Khaleel to prevent the boundary

Nortje to Nitish Reddy, no run, ouch! Nitish Reddy cops a blow on his box and he's down for the count - short and angling into the right-hander, Nitish was hurried by Nortje's pace as he shaped for the pull and missed

The physio comes to have a look and Nitish takes some time to compose himself, that'll give the Capitals a chance to gather and plan out the final phase of the innings. He' still in pain though and needs some more treatment

Fastest to 200 by a team in IPL 14.1 - RCB vs PBKS, Bengaluru, 2016 (15 over match) 14.4 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 14.5 - SRH vs DC, Delhi, today* 14.6 - SRH vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2024 15.2 - KKR vs DC, Vizag, 2024

Nortje to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, just over mid-wicket, Axar ran back and then strtched out with his right hand, but the ball wa salways falling in front of him - was short and into the body, a cramped Nitish still went for the pull and mistimed it badly

Nortje to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, banged in short and at the left-hander, Shahbaz Ahmed swivels across on the pull and misses, he reckons it's too high, no wide called and he reviews - it's another 50-50 call, will it go in favour of Nortje? The 3rd umpire is having several looks and says it's a fair delivery - SRH lose a review
Nortje to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, fuller length delivery on off, Shahbaz stays in the crease and drives it wide of cover, comes back for the second
Nortje to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, back of a length and angling across the left-hander, punched to deep cover for a single
Kuldeep Yadav [3.0-0-44-3] is back into the attack
Kuldeep Yadav to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, slapped to deep point for a single
Kuldeep Yadav to Nitish Reddy, no run, tossed up and sliding across the right-hander, left alone and Nitish is surprised that it's not called as a wide, but they don't review
Kuldeep Yadav to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, flighted delivery on middle, Nitish goes back and works it through mid-wicket, scurries back for the second

Kuldeep Yadav to Nitish Reddy, SIX, beautifully played, quick hands from Nitish - Kuldeep saw him changing stance and fired one just outside off - Nitish goes through with the reverse slap and deposits into the crowd at third man
Kuldeep Yadav to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, Nitish shimmies down the pitch, takes the ball on the full and whips it through mid-wicket for a couple
Kuldeep Yadav to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kuldeep Yadav to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Warner!! A mishit and Kuldeep has four for the night. He has taken a battering, but he has also taken crucial wickets, was dropped short and Nitish shaped for the pull, the idea was right, but he got it right off the bottom of the bat - plenty of height and no real distance, a simple catch for Warner at long-on. Nitish Reddy c Warner b Kuldeep Yadav 37(27) [4s-2 6s-2]
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar [2.0-0-32-0] is back into the attack
Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, back of a length from round the wicket, punched square on the off-side for a single
Mukesh Kumar to Abdul Samad, FOUR, drilled, overpitched and wide of off - Samad needs no sighters as he hammers the drive through extra-cover, raced away at the rate of knots
Mukesh, from round the wicket
Mukesh Kumar to Abdul Samad, 2 runs, high full-toss, but this is below waist high, Samad mishits the slog, but gets enough to clear mid-wicket, back for the second
Mukesh Kumar to Abdul Samad, 1 run, full and well wide of off, driven down to long-off for a single
Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, low full-toss outside off, punched down to long-off for a single

Mukesh Kumar to Abdul Samad, no run, much better from Mukesh, goes for the wide yorker and Samad can't reach out, 9 off the over. SRH have reviewed for the wide call, but the ball has pitched inside the tramline and they've lost their 2nd review as well
Khaleel Ahmed [2.0-0-32-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, Shahbaz is early into the slog and drags it off the inner half, just a single to long-on
Khaleel Ahmed to Abdul Samad, no run, nicely bowled, Khaleel takes the pace off on this slower cutter and pushes it across the right-hander, Samad swings wildly and misses

Khaleel Ahmed to Abdul Samad, SIX, Samad's picked the bones off this though, was another slower ball from Khaleel - but he's pitched it in the slot and watches it disappear over wide long-on as Samad bludgeons the drive

Khaleel Ahmed to Abdul Samad, byes, 1 run, much better from Khaleel, shortens the length and pushes one across the right-hander - Samad shuffles across and is undone by the change of pace, the ball bounces awkwardly in front of Pant and he can't stop it cleanly, allowing a bye

Khaleel Ahmed to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, you can't miss your length on this ground - tad too full from Khaleel, right into Shahbaz's striking zone - he swings it cleanly and sends it sailing over long-on for another maximum
Khaleel, from round the wicket
Khaleel Ahmed to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, clobbered, too full and too straight from Khaleel, on the pads and it's whipped away over long leg, the maximum bringing up SRH's 250
Mukesh Kumar to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mukesh Kumar to Abdul Samad, out Caught by Nortje!! Mukesh strikes, but there's hardly any celebrations in the DC camp. He came from round the wicket, kept it full and kept it away from Samad's reach - had to reach out on the drive and he skews it straight into the hands of Nortje at extra-cover. Abdul Samad c Nortje b Mukesh Kumar 13(8) [4s-1 6s-1]
Pat Cummins, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mukesh Kumar to Cummins, 1 run, yorker length delivery on off, dragged off the inner half to long-on for a single
Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, FOUR, another wild swing, a thick outside edge and the ball bounces away to the third man ropes - the fielder was inside the ring and watches it sail over his head
Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Cummins Run Out!! 1 run completed. A run-out at the bowler's end and DC are finishing well. Low full-toss and Shahbaz couldn't get under it on the drive, skewed it over the bowler's head and towards long-off, there was never a second there, but Cummins sacrifices himself to get Shahbaz back on strike. Just needed a decent throw from Stubbs and Mukesh did the rest. Cummins run out (Tristan Stubbs/Mukesh Kumar) 1(1)

Mukesh Kumar to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, a magical innings from Shahbaz and SRH finish with 266, low full-toss outside off - Shahbaz shuffles across, bends down low and then sweeps it over mid-wicket, went flat and hard, and over the ropes

21:16 Local Time, 15:46 GMT, 21:16 IST: Another team that won the toss and asked SRH to bat first and another team that's been sent on a leather hunt. 277, 287 and now 266 - SRH's batting firing on all cylinders and it's once again Travis Head who was the catalyst at the top of the order. The team fifty came in the 3rd over, his fifty came off 16 balls, the team 100 took just 5 overs and they were 125 for 0 at the end of the batting PP. Delhi Capitals looked dead and buried, but they did enjoy a good phase as they reduced the Sunrisers from 131 for 0 to 151 for 4, but Shahbaz then took control, goaded his young and inexperienced partner, Nitish Kumar, and then finished with a flourish. His 29-ball 59* taking his team to a massive total. Chasing 278, MI made 246, chasing 288, RCB made 262 and DC can take comfort from those chases. But scoreboard pressure is a different thing and they'll have to bat extremely well if they're to compete. We should be in for some more fun if they do get close. Back for the chase shortly..
